Liverpool have been finally beaten in the Premier League. The Redsâ€™ hopes of becoming the second team in the Premier League era to go an entire season unbeaten were dashed on Saturday after they fell 3-0 to relegation threatened Watford. Under Arsene Wenger, Arsenal currently hold the record for the longest unbeaten Premier League run with 49 games in 2003-04. Watford ripped open the EPL leaders in a brilliant second-half display. Senegalese winger, Ismaila Sarr scored a brace and layed on the third for Troy Deeney. The shock win also lift Watford above Bournemouth and out of the relegation zone.